[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/aimagelab/novelty-detection/issues/comments/487561459","html_url":"https://github.com/aimagelab/novelty-detection/issues/2#issuecomment-487561459","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/aimagelab/novelty-detection/issues/2","id":487561459,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ4NzU2MTQ1OQ==","user":{"login":"mathue","id":7715489,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3MTU0ODk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7715489?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue","html_url":"https://github.com/mathue","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mathue/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2019-04-29T12:33:55Z","updated_at":"2019-04-29T12:57:05Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Hi Gin,\r\n\r\nfrom the supplementary material of the paper (chapter 7), one can infer \r\nlambda = 1\r\nbatch size = 256\r\nlearning rate = 10^-4\r\nOptimizer = adam\r\nThey stopped their training after a fixed number of 200 epochs (see closed issue) and monitored the LSA-loss (reconstruction loss plus autoregression loss (neg. llk)).\r\nHowever, if I train with these parameters, I only achieve an average AUROC-NS of 0.817 and 0.916 with a batch size of 64. Thus, they probably change some of these parameters for a better convergence. With batch size 256 it does not converge well but maybe I made a mistake. I attached my code for training (I changed the val() functi